@endnode
@node Version "Version"

 @{b}Version@{ub}

 Version number of Homer.
 Not used.

 Default = 2.0

 It is not possible to change this setting using NewHomerPrefs.
 NewHomerPrefs will always save the default value.

@endnode
@node SamplesPath "SamplesPath"

 @{b}SamplesPath@{ub}

 Where the samples are located.

 Default = Samples

 This setting can be changed in NewHomerPrefs, using the menu option.

@endnode
@node WindowXPos "WindowXPos"

 @{b}WindowXPos@{ub}

 Window Characteristics.
 See also @{"WindowYPos" link WindowYPos}.

 Default = 800

@endnode
@node WindowYPos "WindowYPos"

 @{b}WindowYPos@{ub}
 See also @{"WindowXPos" link WindowXPos}.

 Window Characteristics.

 Default = 600

@endnode
@node WinX "WinX"

 @{b}WinX@{ub}

 Suggested starting window inner dimensions.
 If this is too small, according also to @{"ScaleFactor" link ScaleFactor} parameter, it will be set to a sensible value.
 I suggest you not to touch this.
 See also @{"WinY" link WinY}.

 Default = 10

@endnode
@node WinY "WinY"

 @{b}WinY@{ub}

 Suggested starting window inner dimensions.
 If this is too small, according also to @{"ScaleFactor" link ScaleFactor} parameter, it will be set to a sensible value.
 I suggest you not to touch this.
 See also @{"WinX" link WinX}.

 Default = 10

@endnode
@node FrameWidth "FrameWidth"

 @{b}FrameWidth@{ub}

 WARNING!! The value defines the X dimension of a frame into the animation file...
 DO NOT CHANGE IT UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING!

 Default = 26

@endnode
@node AudioDeviceName "AudioDeviceName"

 @{b}AudioDeviceName@{ub}

 Audio Device Characteristics.
 DO NOT CHANGE these unless you know EXACTLY what you are doing!
 Ignored from version 1.8.

 Default = audio.device

@endnode
@node AudioDeviceUnit "AudioDeviceUnit"

 @{b}AudioDeviceUnit@{ub}

 Audio Device Characteristics.
 DO NOT CHANGE these unless you know EXACTLY what you are doing!
 Ignored from version 1.8.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node AudioDevicePri "AudioDevicePri"

 @{b}AudioDevicePri@{ub}

 Audio Device Characteristics.
 DO NOT CHANGE these unless you know EXACTLY what you are doing!
 Ignored from version 1.8.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node AudioVolume "AudioVolume"

 @{b}AudioVolume@{ub}

 Sets the volume for the sound output.
 Good values are 0 to 64.

 Default = 64

@endnode
@node SaveMem "SaveMem"

 @{b}SaveMem@{ub}

 This is 1 by default (ie NHomer will spare memory).
 If set to 0, NewHomer will keep just one copy of the animation in memory.
 Would save about 8k with the standard animation, 3k with the reduced one.

 Default = 1

@endnode
@node ScaleFactor "ScaleFactor"

 @{b}ScaleFactor@{ub}

 Sets the size of the image.
 100% and 1000% are the minimum and maximum values, rounded by steps of 100.
 See also @{"ScaleFactorX" link ScaleFactorX}.

 Default = 100%

@endnode
@node ScaleFactorX "ScaleFactorX"

 @{b}ScaleFactorX@{ub}

 This is a 'X scalefactor' useful for those people using non proportional screens.
 For PAL 640x256, you should set it to 200%, so you will get a 1:1 Homer...
 For 320x512,  you should set ScaleFactorX to 200% and ScaleFactor to 100% (or multiples of these values).
 If you leave it to zero, then only @{"ScaleFactor" link ScaleFactor} will be used to compute both X and Y dimensions.
 100% and 1000% are the minimum and maximum values, rounded by steps of 100.

 Default = 100%

@endnode
@node DoNothing "DoNothing"

 @{b}DoNothing@{ub}

 The weighted chance of Homer doing nothing.
 See also @{"DoBurp" link DoBurp}, @{"DoPleasure" link DoPleasure}, @{"DoDoh" link DoDoh}, @{"DoMood" link DoMood} and @{"DoTalk" link DoTalk}.

 Default = 5

@endnode
@node DoBurp "DoBurp"

 @{b}DoBurp@{ub}

 The weighted chance of Homer playing a sample from the @{"[BurpSamples]" link [BurpSamples]} list.
 See also @{"DoNothing" link DoNothing}, @{"DoPleasure" link DoPleasure}, @{"DoDoh" link DoDoh}, @{"DoMood" link DoMood} and @{"DoTalk" link DoTalk}.

 Default = 5

@endnode
@node DoPleasure "DoPleasure"

 @{b}DoPleasure@{ub}

 The weighted chance of Homer playing a sample from the @{"[PleasureSamples]" link [PleasureSamples]} list.
 See also @{"DoNothing" link DoNothing}, @{"DoBurp" link DoBurp}, @{"DoDoh" link DoDoh}, @{"DoMood" link DoMood} and @{"DoTalk" link DoTalk}.

 Default = 5

@endnode
@node DoDoh "DoDoh"

 @{b}DoDoh@{ub}

 The weighted chance of Homer playing a sample from the @{"[DohSamples]" link [DohSamples]} list.
 See also @{"DoNothing" link DoNothing}, @{"DoBurp" link DoBurp}, @{"DoPleasure" link DoPleasure}, @{"DoMood" link DoMood} and @{"DoTalk" link DoTalk}.

 Default = 5

@endnode
@node DoMood "DoMood"

 @{b}DoMood@{ub}

 The weighted chance of Homer changing mood.
 See also @{"DoNothing" link DoNothing}, @{"DoBurp" link DoBurp}, @{"DoPleasure" link DoPleasure}, @{"DoDoh" link DoDoh} and @{"DoTalk" link DoTalk}.

 Default = 20

@endnode
@node DoTalk "DoTalk"

 @{b}DoTalk@{ub}

 The weighted chance of Homer playing a sample.
 See also @{"DoNothing" link DoNothing}, @{"DoBurp" link DoBurp}, @{"DoPleasure" link DoPleasure}, @{"DoDoh" link DoDoh} and @{"DoMood" link DoMood}.

 Default = 60

@endnode
@node ManyDohChance "ManyDohChance"

 @{b}ManyDohChance@{ub}

 Set the chance of Homer saying Doh after initially saying it.
 See also @{"ManyDohContChance" link ManyDohContChance}.

 Default = 10%

@endnode
@node ManyDohContChance "ManyDohContChance"

 @{b}ManyDohContChance@{ub}

 Chance of Homer continuing to say Doh.
 Ignored by some versions.
 See also @{"ManyDohChance" link ManyDohChance}.

 Default = 80%

@endnode
@node ActivateWindow "ActivateWindow"

 @{b}ActivateWindow@{ub}

 Activate Homer's window at startup.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node InitialMood "InitialMood"

 @{b}InitialMood@{ub}

 Starting mood of Homer.
 Possible values are:
 0 - random
 1 - happy
 2 - angry
 3 - sad
 4 - pleasure
 See also @{"StartSampleMood" link StartSampleMood}, @{"FinalMood" link FinalMood}, @{"IconifyMood" link IconifyMood} and @{"DeIconifyMood" link DeIconifyMood}.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node StartSampleMood "StartSampleMood"

 @{b}StartSampleMood@{ub}

 The mood of Homer while playing starting sample.
 Only makes sense when there are some samples in the @{"[StartSamples]" link [StartSamples]} list.
 Accepted values are:
 0 - random
 1 - happy
 2 - angry
 3 - sad
 4 - pleasure
 5 - belch
 6 - doh
 See also @{"InitialMood" link InitialMood}, @{"FinalMood" link FinalMood}, @{"IconifyMood" link IconifyMood} and @{"DeIconifyMood" link DeIconifyMood}.

 Default = 1

@endnode
@node FinalMood "FinalMood"

 @{b}FinalMood@{ub}

 The mood of Homer while playing ending sample.
 Only makes sense when there are some samples in the @{"[EndSamples]" link [EndSamples]} list.
 Accepted values are:
 0 - keep current (pseudo-random)
 1 - happy
 2 - angry
 3 - sad
 4 - pleasure
 5 - belch
 6 - doh
 See also @{"InitialMood" link InitialMood}, @{"StartSampleMood" link StartSampleMood}, @{"IconifyMood" link IconifyMood} and @{"DeIconifyMood" link DeIconifyMood}.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node IconifyMood "IconifyMood"

 @{b}IconifyMood@{ub}

 The mood of Homer while being iconified.
 Only makes sense when there are some samples in the @{"[IconifySamples]" link [IconifySamples]} list.
 Accepted values are:
 0 - random
 1 - happy
 2 - angry
 3 - sad
 4 - pleasure
 5 - belch
 6 - doh
 See also @{"InitialMood" link InitialMood}, @{"StartSampleMood" link StartSampleMood}, @{"FinalMood" link FinalMood} and @{"DeIconifyMood" link DeIconifyMood}.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node DeIconifyMood "DeIconifyMood"

 @{b}DeIconifyMood@{ub}

 The mood of Homer while being deiconified.
 Only makes sense when there are some samples in the @{"[DeIconifySamples]" link [DeIconifySamples]} list.
 Accepted values are:
 0 - random
 1 - happy
 2 - angry
 3 - sad
 4 - pleasure
 5 - belch
 6 - doh
 See also @{"InitialMood" link InitialMood}, @{"StartSampleMood" link StartSampleMood}, @{"FinalMood" link FinalMood} and @{"IconifyMood" link IconifyMood}.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node LookLeft "LookLeft"

 @{b}LookLeft@{ub}

 Set to 1 to make Homer look towards left or 0 to emulate old Homer.

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node FollowMouse "FollowMouse"

 @{b}FollowMouse@{ub}

 Don't set this one to 1 if you don't want to slow down senseless your machine.
 Only recommended if you really want it AND have a fast Amiga (68030 or better)
 It is a MUST only for UAE users... ;))

 Default = 0

@endnode
@node NoExitSample "NoExitSample"

 @{b}NoExitSample@{ub}

 Set this not to have Homer playing a sample when exiting.
 Notice that setting this to non-zero will stop also playing when there is a list of @{"[EndSamples]" link [EndSamples]}.

 Default = 0

 This setting has no direct gadget in NewHomerPrefs.
 NewHomerPrefs will change this setting accordingly, when you add or remove @{"[EndSamples]" link [EndSamples]}.

@endnode
@node DelayTime "DelayTime"

 @{b}DelayTime@{ub}

 The time in seconds Homer waits before trying to do something.

 Default = 8

@endnode
